paper_abstract: We introduce a general model of random context multiset grammars as well as the concept of multiset random context checkers and transducers. Our main results show how recursively enumerable sets of finite multisets can be generated using these models of computing; corresponding results for antiport P systems are established, too. paper_title: Multiset random context grammars, checkers, and transducers
